<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,1788,1920]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1823,1848]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Notes.</emphasis>
Reported to be a cleptoparasite of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1868" box="[665,884,1823,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compactus">
<emphasis box="[665,884,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Colletes compactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Rozen &amp; Favreau" box="[943,1207,1823,1848]" firstAuthor="Rozen" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="106 - 111" refId="ref101425" refString="Rozen, J. G. &amp; Favreau, M. S. (1968) Biological notes on Colletes compactus compactus and its cuckoo bee, Epeolus pusillus (Hymenoptera: Colletidae and Anthophoridae). Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 76, 106 - 111." type="journal article" year="1968">Rozen &amp; Favreau 1968</bibRefCitation>
), but the small body size of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1864" box="[236,356,1860,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Epeolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[236,356,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">E. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its limited occurrence in certain localities (e.g., Tompkins County, New York) suggest an alternative or additional association with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cresson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[613,777,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Epeolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[613,777,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">C. americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ascher" box="[836,1046,1895,1920]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ascher" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="47 - 71" refId="ref82512" refString="Ascher, J. S., Kornbluth, S. &amp; Goelet, R. G. (2014) Bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila) of Gardiners Island, Suffolk County, New York. Northeastern Naturalist, 21, 47 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1656 / 045.021.0105" type="journal article" year="2014">
Ascher 
<emphasis box="[922,978,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
